@page "/privacy-policy"

<div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>GoalBlaze</strong> ("We") collects, uses, and protects the personal information you provide on our website and through our services related to goal tracking, progress monitoring, user authentication, customization, and motivational support.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Personal Information: When you register for an account, we may collect your name and email address to create and manage your account.</li>
        <li>Goal-related Data: When you use our goal tracking features, you may enter goal descriptions, target deadlines, and other related information.</li>
        <li>User Preferences: We may collect information about your preferences, such as your choice between dark mode and light mode.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Providing and improving our goal tracking and progress monitoring services.</li>
        <li>Customizing your user experience based on your preferences.</li>
        <li>Securely authenticating you for accessing goal-related data across devices.</li>
        <li>Sending notifications for goal progress or updates.</li>
        <li>Displaying motivational quotes to inspire your journey.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        We take the security of your data seriously and implement measures to protect it, including encryption, regular security assessments, and limited access to authorized personnel or systems.
    </p>

    <h2>User Rights</h2>
    <p>
        You have the right to access, update, or delete your goal-related data. You can also unsubscribe from notifications or delete your account at any time. For assistance with these actions, please contact our support team.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party Integrations</h2>
    <p>
        We may integrate with third-party services for goal tracking, authentication, or motivational content. Your data may be shared with or accessed by these third parties in accordance with their privacy policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Updates to the Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
    </p>
</div>

